cs.cscollections.stack
Class ArrayStack<T>

java.lang.Object
  cs.cscollections.stack.ArrayStack<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
StackADT<T>
public class ArrayStack<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements StackADT<T>

The ArrayStack implements a traditional stack collection using an array implementation. An ArrayStack object will dynamically resize when an object is added to a full stack.

Version:
v 1.0 3/2016

S. Sigman

size

public int size()

size returns the number of elemenst in the stack. Caution, size returns the number of elements pushed on the stack and not the capacity of the stack.

Returns:
The number of elements that have been pushed on the stack and not popped off. i.e. The current number of elements in the stack.
